Description: Corner-fragment of a grey basalt naos(?); four columns of incised hieroglyphic text on one surface, part of another column visible on another.
Curator's comments: The text relates to royal and cult activities of a traditional pharaonic Egyptian type. The nature of the monument and the content of its text are under study by David Klotz.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (BB.07)
